# EROSCAPE — .cursorrules
# Versión: 2.0 Gamificada
# Stack: Next.js 16 · React 19 · TypeScript 5 · Tailwind CSS v4 · Framer Motion · Lucide React

## PROJECT CONTEXT

Eroscape is a premium adult erotic escape room booking platform.
The UI is dark, luxurious, immersive, and GAMIFIED.
The product is NOT explicit — it is elegant, sensual, and adult-oriented.
Privacy and discretion are core UX requirements at all times.

The booking flow is a 5-ACT NARRATIVE, not a form.
Every screen is a level. Every choice has visual consequences.
The user is the protagonist of the story.

---

## TECH STACK — NEVER DEVIATE

- Framework: Next.js 16 with App Router (NOT Pages Router)
- Language: TypeScript 5 — strict mode, no `any` types ever
- Styling: Tailwind CSS v4 — use CSS variables via var() for brand colors
- Animation: Framer Motion — for all transitions and interactions
- Icons: Lucide React — no other icon library
- UI Primitives: hand-built (no shadcn, no radix in prototype)
- State: React Context + custom hooks (no Redux, no Zustand in prototype)
- Forms: controlled components with React state (no react-hook-form in prototype)
- Canvas: native HTML5 Canvas for ParticleField and signature pad

---

## FILE STRUCTURE

- Pages:           src/app/(public)/[route]/page.tsx
- Auth pages:      src/app/(auth)/[route]/page.tsx
- API routes:      src/app/api/[route]/route.ts
- Reusable UI:     src/components/ui/
- Page sections:   src/components/sections/
- Booking flow:    src/components/booking/
- Dashboard:       src/components/dashboard/
- Custom hooks:    src/hooks/use[Name].ts
- Types:           src/types/[domain].ts
- Utilities:       src/lib/utils.ts
- Constants:       src/lib/constants.ts
- Archetype logic: src/lib/archetype.ts

---

## TYPESCRIPT RULES

- Strict mode always on
- Never use `any` — use `unknown` then narrow
- All props: explicit TypeScript interface named `[ComponentName]Props`
- Use `const` assertions for static data arrays in constants.ts
- Export types as named exports from src/types/
- No implicit returns in JSX-returning functions

---

## COMPONENT RULES

- Named exports everywhere (default exports ONLY for page.tsx files)
- File name = component name in PascalCase
- One component per file (small sub-components in same file are OK)
- 'use client' only when strictly necessary
- Server components by default
- Props destructured at function signature

```typescript
// ✅ CORRECT
export function ExperienceCard({ title, intensity, missionCode }: ExperienceCardProps) {
  const handleSelect = () => { /* logic */ }
  return (...)
}

// ❌ WRONG
export default function Card(props: any) {
  return <button onClick={() => { complexLogic() }}>...</button>
}
```

---

## STYLING RULES

- Tailwind utilities as primary method
- Brand colors ALWAYS via CSS var(): var(--color-magenta), NEVER hardcoded hex in JSX
- Responsive: mobile-first always (sm: md: lg: breakpoints)
- Dark backgrounds only — no white/light except PanicMode
- Hover + focus + active states always defined
- Focus rings always visible (accessibility non-negotiable)
- No inline style={{ }} except for dynamic values Tailwind cannot express
- Use cn() from clsx + tailwind-merge for conditional classes
- Intensity-reactive backgrounds use CSS custom property --current-bg driven by JS

---

## ANIMATION RULES — FRAMER MOTION

- Variants defined OUTSIDE the component (no inline variant objects in JSX)
- All entrance animations: fade + translate (never scale alone)
- Durations: micro-interactions 0.15s · UI transitions 0.3s · page reveals 0.6s · hero 0.8s
- Easing: always cubic-bezier(0.25, 0.46, 0.45, 0.94) for the "sensual" feel
- Always check prefers-reduced-motion via useReducedMotion()
- AnimatePresence required for any conditional mount/unmount with animation
- No layout shift animations on mobile (performance)
- Milestone animations (seal, access granted, archetype reveal): can be longer (1-2s), dramatic

```typescript
// ✅ CORRECT
const cardVariants = {
  hidden: { opacity: 0, y: 20 },
  visible: { opacity: 1, y: 0, transition: { duration: 0.4, ease: [0.25, 0.46, 0.45, 0.94] } }
}
export function ExperienceCard() {
  return <motion.div variants={cardVariants} initial="hidden" animate="visible" />
}
```

