## WHAT TO NEVER DO

- Never use `any` TypeScript type
- Never hardcode brand colors as hex in JSX/TSX files
- Never use Pages Router (App Router only)
- Never use default exports except page.tsx files
- Never use setTimeout for animations (use Framer Motion)
- Never store payment data in localStorage/sessionStorage
- Never add console.log (use console.error for real errors only)
- Never make components over 200 lines without splitting
- Never use libraries not in package.json without asking
- Never generate explicit/pornographic content, descriptions, or image prompts
- Never skip the prefers-reduced-motion check on animated components
- Never use `any` — seriously, never
- Never use military vocabulary (mission, operation, agent, classified, protocol) in user-facing copy
- Never make the user feel they are being evaluated — they are being desired and welcomed
- The tone is always: welcoming darkness, not threatening darkness
